Awesime (A Widely Extensible SIMulation Environment) is an
object-oriented library for process-oriented simulation.  It can be
configured for MIPS R2000/R3000, Sun SPARC, Motorola 68k and 88k, Intel
i386, National Semiconductor NS32K, and DEC Alpha.  It is written in
C++ and is available via anonymous FTP from the University of Colorado,
Boulder: ftp.cs.colorado.edu in the directory /pub/cs/distribs/Awesime.
